This paper is about speech recognition, which is a subfield of natural language processing (NLP) and falls under the computer science category of "Computation and Language" (cs.CL). The paper also involves machine learning techniques, specifically attention-based encoder-decoder models, which could fall under "Machine Learning" (cs.LG) or "Artificial Intelligence" (cs.AI). Additionally, the paper discusses the impact of modeling units on speech recognition, which could be considered a subfield of signal processing (cs.SI) or data mining (cs.SD).
